00:28.090 --> 00:30.892
<i>The latest in a long line
of racially charged incidents</i>

00:30.960 --> 00:32.891
<i>occurred yesterday, rocking the city.</i>

00:32.916 --> 00:34.774
<i>Last night, 15-year-old Andre Watkins</i>

00:34.799 --> 00:36.946
<i>was accidentally shot
and killed by the police</i>

00:36.971 --> 00:38.665
<i>as he played basketball
with his friends.</i>

00:38.690 --> 00:39.968
15 years old.

00:40.036 --> 00:41.803
Just a few years older than my son.

00:41.871 --> 00:43.934
<i>The police believed Andre was armed</i>

00:43.959 --> 00:46.727
<i>and that he'd been involved in a
robbery that occurred nearby.</i>

00:46.795 --> 00:49.296
<i>He matched a description of the suspect.</i>

00:49.364 --> 00:50.965
Let me guess... "black" and "male".

00:51.033 --> 00:53.501
That's a little harsh.
You weren't there.

00:53.568 --> 00:55.069
I've been there plenty of times.

00:55.137 --> 00:57.571
Including when you actually
committed a crime, of course.

00:57.639 --> 01:00.875
<i>As citizens of this great city, we
all have a choice in this moment...</i>

01:01.042 --> 01:05.078
<i>Lash out or band together
in peace, in strength.</i>

01:05.147 --> 01:08.549
<i>I urge every one of you,
remain calm and obey the law.</i>

01:08.617 --> 01:09.750
No pajamas today?

01:09.818 --> 01:11.786
My brother let me out of the doghouse

01:11.853 --> 01:13.678
and back into his apartment.

01:13.703 --> 01:15.689
The bed is more comfortable
than my couch,

01:15.757 --> 01:17.958
but I do miss walking around
the office naked.

01:18.026 --> 01:19.760
I'm never sitting in any
of these chairs again.

01:19.828 --> 01:21.249
<i>On behalf of everyone
in law enforcement,</i>

01:21.274 --> 01:23.652
<i>I extend our deepest
condolences to Andre's family.</i>

01:23.699 --> 01:26.100
Wallace might not be able to
keep the lid on this powder keg.

01:26.168 --> 01:29.437
He can't. But we can hit it head on.

01:31.840 --> 01:34.075
Mitchell Alan... African-American.

01:34.142 --> 01:36.977
The prosecutor refereed to him
as "King Kong" at trial.

01:37.045 --> 01:39.013
He got 15 years for armed robbery.

01:40.348 --> 01:41.949
Or Levon Cartwright...

01:42.017 --> 01:43.884
also black... shot and killed

01:43.952 --> 01:46.454
a white trespasser
claiming self-defense,

01:46.521 --> 01:47.955
serving 25 years,

01:48.023 --> 01:50.324
unlike a white defendant
in a similar case

01:50.392 --> 01:52.326
who received a suspended sentence.

01:52.394 --> 01:53.794
I'm sensing a theme here.

01:53.862 --> 01:55.896
- Oh.
- Susan Jefferson,

01:55.964 --> 01:58.532
serving life for killing
her abusive boyfriend.

01:58.600 --> 02:00.201
Her court-appointed lawyer

02:00.268 --> 02:02.737
was a card-carrying member of the KKK.

02:02.804 --> 02:04.271
What about Porscha Williams?

02:05.340 --> 02:08.609
No. That's a bad idea.

02:09.020 --> 02:11.188
If by bad you mean perfect, I agree.

02:11.213 --> 02:13.080
Porscha Williams is
a radical black activist

02:13.148 --> 02:14.884
serving life for murdering a white cop.

02:14.909 --> 02:17.251
After having her trial moved out
of the city to Albany

02:17.319 --> 02:20.420
and being found guilty by an
all-white jury in under three hours.

02:20.445 --> 02:22.022
Just because they were white
doesn't mean they were wrong.

02:22.090 --> 02:25.793
She was seen shooting an NYPD officer
when her peace rally turned into a riot.

02:25.861 --> 02:27.428
A riot, a riot.

02:27.496 --> 02:29.263
Why do I feel like if it was
a group of white people,

02:29.331 --> 02:30.771
you'd be calling it a demonstration?

02:30.832 --> 02:32.299
Call it what you will, the demonstrators

02:32.367 --> 02:33.934
did not cooperate with the police.

02:34.002 --> 02:36.437
Who showed up in riot gear like
a bunch of storm troopers.

02:36.505 --> 02:38.506
Have you ever been hit
with a rock or a bottle?

02:38.573 --> 02:40.808
It hurts no matter what race
is throwing it at you.

02:40.876 --> 02:42.476
- That's...
- Could we all please just...

02:42.544 --> 02:43.778
What, get along? Hell no.

02:43.845 --> 02:45.780
This is more fun, more honest,
more productive.

02:45.847 --> 02:48.282
It's a case, not a conversation starter.

02:48.350 --> 02:49.517
It can be both.

02:49.584 --> 02:51.385
A black teenager was just killed
by the cops.

02:51.453 --> 02:53.954
Do we really want to take on
something so racially charged?

02:54.022 --> 02:56.490
The city needs to know that the
CIU is fighting for justice,

02:56.558 --> 03:00.528
which is supposed to be blind
but is clearly not color-blind.

03:00.595 --> 03:02.463
Porscha's case gets another look.

